p: \bVery well, sir. Everything seems in order.
\bNow that we have a blood sample, we can organize a time and place for you to get vaccinated.
\bWe must ask, sir, have you noticed any of your friends and family exhibit odd behavior?
\bWell, a few of my friends have been acting differently lately...
\bThen we ask that you report them, sir.\nThey absolutely must be vaccinated or quarantined for the safety of Torren.
\bFantastic, sir. We've already examined at least thirty people!
\b...I can't believe it was this easy.
\bThat stupid child and that foolish old man gave us the perfect excuse to collect the DNA of everyone in the region.
\b...err, sir, why does the Infernal Cult need the DNA of so many people?
\b...why don't you... forget that I said that.
\bGood. Continue to work and let me know if anyone... important shows up.
\bDon't you dare cut in front of me!
\rI wonder what's in this vaccine? I heard from one of my friends they didn't actually put anything in...
\rIt's like they just took a blood sample. How weird.
\bI got in line as soon as I heard what was happening.
\bI'm ready to get vaccinated to protect the region!
\bAnd I'm ready to report all my friends who refuse!
\bUm, hello. Thank you for coming, ma'am.
\bUm, hello. Thank you for coming, sir.
\bIf you would, I'd just like you to sign-
\bCongratulations! You're the 100th citizen to come sign up!
\bPlease come to the back with me to collect your... reward!
